The paper deals with the design of mechanisms for profit maximization, which is a central topic in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses techniques from machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.DS) to analyze the sample complexity of these mechanisms. Finally, the paper is concerned with the economics of mechanism design (cs.EC), which is a subfield of computer science that studies the design of incentives in multi-agent systems.
